Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.85,0:00:59.67,辉注,,0,0,0,,其实如果飞船能以光速飞行 就不需要休眠了\N因为飞船上的时间会很短
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.10,0:00:05.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,很多涉及到深空旅行的科幻电影中
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.10,0:00:05.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,Watch almost any film involving deep space travel apart from the fantasy ones
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.67,0:00:10.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,你会发现人们从休眠中醒来时
Dialogue: 2,0:00:05.67,0:00:10.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,and you'll see people going into or coming out of stasis
Dialogue: 1,0:00:10.12,0:00:13.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,苏醒的过程通常看上去非常不愉快
Dialogue: 2,0:00:10.12,0:00:13.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,of which the waking up part usually looks quite unpleasant
Dialogue: 1,0:00:13.77,0:00:17.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这种用于长期太空旅行的诱导休眠技术
Dialogue: 2,0:00:13.77,0:00:17.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,but could this type of induced hibernation for longer space journeys
Dialogue: 1,0:00:17.90,0:00:21.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,能在不远的将来变成现实吗？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:17.90,0:00:21.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,become a reality in the not so distant future.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.12,0:00:37.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,以我们现有的火箭科技 在太阳系内旅行得越远
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.12,0:00:37.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,The farther we travel in to the solar system with our current transport technology,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:37.57,0:00:39.55,辉中,,0,0,0,,花的时间就越长
Dialogue: 2,0:00:37.57,0:00:39.55,辉英,,0,0,0,,the longer it takes to get anywhere,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.55,0:00:44.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,短则去火星的五个月 长则去外行星的10年
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.55,0:00:44.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,from about 5 months to mars up to around 10 years to get to the outer planet
Dialogue: 1,0:00:44.87,0:00:48.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,更不用说恒星际旅行了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:44.87,0:00:48.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,and that's without even thinking about traveling to the stars.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.90,0:00:54.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,以我们现有科技 去最近的比邻星要七万年
Dialogue: 2,0:00:48.90,0:00:54.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,The nearest Proxima Centauri would take about 70,000 years with our current tech.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.85,0:00:59.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使我们能以光速旅行 整个旅程也要花四年
Dialogue: 2,0:00:54.85,0:00:59.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even if we could travel at the speed of light it's over a 4 year journey.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.02,0:01:04.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,这对于探测器来说没什么 但就像之前说过的一样
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.02,0:01:04.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is fine for robotic space probes but as it has been said before,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:04.10,0:01:09.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,只要加入了人 那问题可就多了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:04.10,0:01:09.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,as soon as you add humans into the mix the issues go up by an order of magnitude.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:09.55,0:01:12.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,让人在上面呆上几年
Dialogue: 2,0:01:09.55,0:01:12.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,Having people awake a roaming around for years
Dialogue: 1,0:01:12.20,0:01:17.60,辉中,,0,0,0,,不但要消耗大量资源来保证维持宇航员的生命
Dialogue: 2,0:01:12.20,0:01:17.60,辉英,,0,0,0,,not only takes up much more in the way of resources to feed them and keeping them alive
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.60,0:01:21.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,还会造成精神问题 比如无聊 孤独
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.60,0:01:21.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,but there are the psychological issues of boredom, loneliness
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.42,0:01:26.37,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果有人因此犯罪 还会让狭小的飞船中的人们神经紧绷
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.42,0:01:26.37,辉英,,0,0,0,,and just getting on each others‘ nerves trapped in a small spacecraft
Dialogue: 1,0:01:26.37,0:01:30.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果有人因此犯罪 还会让狭小的飞船中的人们神经紧绷
Dialogue: 2,0:01:26.37,0:01:30.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,for as long or longer than someones gets for committing a serious crime.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.00,0:01:36.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果我们可以让人类进入一种休眠状态 则会解决很多问题
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.00,0:01:36.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,If we could put people into some form of hibernation it would solve a lot of these issues.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.37,0:01:42.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,如果旅程多数时间都在睡觉 那居住舱可以做得又轻又小
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.37,0:01:42.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,If they are asleep for most of the journey then the space habitats themselves can also be smaller and lighter
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.50,0:01:47.65,辉中,,0,0,0,,相比全程清醒的乘员 就需要带更少的燃料 更少的发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.50,0:01:47.65,辉英,,0,0,0,,so less propellant and rockets engines are required compared to a fully awake crew.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.00,0:01:53.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,还能加装更多的防护罩以抵抗宇宙射线
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.00,0:01:53.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,This would also allow more shielding against cosmic radiation which is probably
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.22,0:01:56.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这可能才是长期太空飞行的最大问题
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.22,0:01:56.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,the biggest issue for long-duration space flights.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.66,0:02:02.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,即使对于火星任务 这也会对飞船构型带来巨大改变
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.66,0:02:02.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,Even on a mars mission, it could make a substantial difference to the craft configuration.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.12,0:02:08.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,人们也希望这能缓解些许失重带来的肌肉萎缩与骨质流失等影响
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.12,0:02:08.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,It's hoped that it could also reduce some of the effects of weightlessness such as muscle and bone loss.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.50,0:02:11.87,辉中,,0,0,0,,然而 我们不是天生会休眠的物种
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.50,0:02:11.87,辉英,,0,0,0,,However, we are not a naturally hibernating species
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.87,0:02:16.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们在生理上也无法适应不靠外界帮助进入任意时长的休眠状态
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.87,0:02:16.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,and we don't have the biological adaptations to enter such state
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.07,0:02:20.57,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们在生理上也无法适应不靠外界帮助进入任意时长的休眠状态
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.07,0:02:20.57,辉英,,0,0,0,,and stay in it for any length of time without outside help.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.95,0:02:24.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们当前拥有的最接近的技术是低温疗法
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.95,0:02:24.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,The nearest thing we have at the moment is Therapeutic Hypothermia
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.77,0:02:29.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,在某些医疗程序和创伤治疗中很有名
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.77,0:02:29.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,which is well known and used in certain medical procedures and trauma treatments
Dialogue: 1,0:02:29.50,0:02:32.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这和休眠是不同的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:29.50,0:02:32.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,but this is not the same as hibernation.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.47,0:02:38.16,辉中,,0,0,0,,其他诱导休眠的办法诸如吸入硫化氢气体曾被用于小白鼠
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.47,0:02:38.16,辉英,,0,0,0,,Other methods of inducing torpor such as inhaling Hydrogen Sulfide has been used in mice
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.16,0:02:41.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以减少细胞的氧气需求量
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.16,0:02:41.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,to reduce the cellular demand for oxygen
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.40,0:02:46.64,辉中,,0,0,0,,研究当中 小鼠大脑中一组专门的神经元被抑制
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.40,0:02:46.64,辉英,,0,0,0,,and research into inhibiting a specialized group of neurons in the brains of rats
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.64,0:02:51.67,辉中,,0,0,0,,从而阻断其体温调节中比如颤抖之类的冷反射
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.64,0:02:51.67,辉英,,0,0,0,,to block the bodies thermo-regulatory cold defense like shivering
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.67,0:02:56.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,在诱导体温降低的同时还会增加心率
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.67,0:02:56.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,and increasing the heart rate when the body temperature drops are also being conducted.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.22,0:03:03.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,人类等哺乳动物进化出了独立于外界温度的恒定体温
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.22,0:03:03.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,We humans and other mammals have evolved to have a constant body temperature independent of the ambient conditions.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.95,0:03:07.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,这在进化上给了我们更大的优势 让我们有更广的活动范围
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.95,0:03:07.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,This gives us an evolutionary advantage for increased mobility
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.90,0:03:11.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,但也让我们有了更快的代谢速率
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.90,0:03:11.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,but it also means we have a high metabolic rate,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.52,0:03:16.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们比休眠的动物需要更多的食物 排出更多废物
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.52,0:03:16.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,we need a lot more food and produce more waste than animals in hibernation.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.85,0:03:24.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以关键是在不损伤机体的情况下减慢代谢速率
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.85,0:03:24.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,Slowing this metabolic rate is the key goal but without causing damage to the body in the process.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:24.42,0:03:29.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,动物有两种休眠方式来抵御
Dialogue: 2,0:03:24.42,0:03:29.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,There are two types of hibernation which animals use to help them survive conditions
Dialogue: 1,0:03:29.40,0:03:36.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,诸如冬天的严寒 干燥 酷热或食物匮乏
Dialogue: 2,0:03:29.40,0:03:36.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as harsh cold winters, very dry and hot periods or when their seasonable food is unavailable.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.62,0:03:40.40,辉中,,0,0,0,,这两种状态分别叫真冬眠和昏睡
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.62,0:03:40.40,辉英,,0,0,0,,These two states are true hibernation and torpor.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.82,0:03:43.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,真冬眠是动物自愿的状态
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.82,0:03:43.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,True hibernation is a voluntary state
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.20,0:03:49.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,动物会提前积累脂肪 之后进入深度睡眠状态
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.20,0:03:49.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,where the animal prepares by building up fat reserves and then goes into a truly deep state of sleep
Dialogue: 1,0:03:49.15,0:03:55.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,其间体温、心率、呼吸、代谢速率都会极大降低
Dialogue: 2,0:03:49.15,0:03:55.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,whereby the bodies temperature, heart rate, breathing, and metabolic rate all dramatically slow down.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.10,0:04:03.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,以花栗鼠为例 冬眠时心率可以从每分钟350下降低到每分钟4下
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.10,0:04:03.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,A chipmunk, for example, can lower its heart rate from 350 bpm to just 4bpm during hibernation
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.22,0:04:07.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,很多动物会在这期间消耗身体一半的重量
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.22,0:04:07.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,and many animals can lose up to half their body weight during this time.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.55,0:04:09.93,辉中,,0,0,0,,昏睡也像是深度睡眠的状态
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.55,0:04:09.93,辉英,,0,0,0,,Torpor is like a very deep sleep state
Dialogue: 1,0:04:09.93,0:04:14.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,也会降低体温、心率、呼吸和代谢速率
Dialogue: 2,0:04:09.93,0:04:14.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the low body temperature, heart rate, breathing and metabolic rate of hibernation
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.02,0:04:21.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,但时长根据物种从一晚到数月不等
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.02,0:04:21.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,but this can last from a normal night sleep cycle to months depending on the species.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.37,0:04:27.44,辉中,,0,0,0,,黑熊的这个状态有3-5个月 其间会定期醒来
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.37,0:04:27.44,辉英,,0,0,0,,Black Bears enter this state for 3-5 months with regular wake up periods
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.58,0:04:33.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,它们甚至可以循环体内的含氮废物 防止肌肉萎缩
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.58,0:04:33.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they can even recycle Nitrogen waste from the bodies, preventing muscle atrophy.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.35,0:04:36.77,辉中,,0,0,0,,昏睡状态下的动物也能醒来
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.35,0:04:36.77,辉英,,0,0,0,,Animals in a state of torpor can also wake up,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.77,0:04:41.81,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这可能需要一小时甚至更多 才能让一切恢复原本的速度
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.77,0:04:41.81,辉英,,0,0,0,,though it takes maybe an hour or more to do so and bring everything up to speed.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.81,0:04:45.25,辉中,,0,0,0,,这两者中 昏睡可能是对我们最有用的
Dialogue: 2,0:04:41.81,0:04:45.25,辉英,,0,0,0,,Out of these two, torpor would be most useful for us
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.25,0:04:49.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为我们可以在紧急情况下或者计划中随时醒来
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.25,0:04:49.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,because of the ability to wake up in an emergency or on schedule.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.10,0:04:55.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,但我们仍然不了解这种状态的细胞层面和分子层面的机制
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.10,0:04:55.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,But we still don't know the cellular and molecular mechanisms of natural suspended animation.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.57,0:05:00.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,人类可以受控进入低体温状态长达14天
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.57,0:05:00.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,People have been kept in a controlled hypothermic state for up to 14 days
Dialogue: 1,0:05:00.27,0:05:02.96,辉中,,0,0,0,,但会有严重的副作用
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.27,0:05:02.96,辉英,,0,0,0,,but there are problems with serious side effects
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.96,0:05:06.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,比如血栓 出血 感染 肝脏损伤
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.96,0:05:06.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,such as blood clots, bleeding, infection and liver damage.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:06.07,0:05:11.35,辉中,,0,0,0,,还需要有定期的营养与液体维持我们身体正常运转
Dialogue: 2,0:05:06.07,0:05:11.35,辉英,,0,0,0,,There is also the need for us to have regular nutrients and fluids keep our bodies working
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.35,0:05:16.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为我们没有冬眠动物有的自然适应力
Dialogue: 2,0:05:11.35,0:05:16.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,as we don't have the natural adaptations that hibernating animals have
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.05,0:05:18.85,辉中,,0,0,0,,这就是我们面对的最大问题
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.05,0:05:18.85,辉英,,0,0,0,,and this is the biggest problem we face.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.27,0:05:23.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,NASA和ESA都在研究诱导昏睡
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.27,0:05:23.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,Both NASA and ESA are working on Torpor inducing habitats
Dialogue: 1,0:05:23.60,0:05:29.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,给人注射镇定剂后冷却 进入轻微的低体温状态
Dialogue: 2,0:05:23.60,0:05:29.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,where the person would be sedated and then cooled, placing them into a mildly hypothermic state.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:29.70,0:05:36.12,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了保证营养与液体供应 他们使用了“完全注射营养液”
Dialogue: 2,0:05:29.70,0:05:36.12,辉英,,0,0,0,,In order to provide the nutrients and fluids a process called Total Parenteral Nutrition is used.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.27,0:05:42.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,该技术通过静脉为人体补充所有必需营养物质
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.27,0:05:42.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,This is feeding a person intravenously with all the essential nutrients and fluids to keep them alive
Dialogue: 1,0:05:42.57,0:05:46.02,辉中,,0,0,0,,通过类似在外周静脉置入中心静脉导管
Dialogue: 2,0:05:42.57,0:05:46.02,辉英,,0,0,0,,with something like a peripherally inserted central catheter.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.30,0:05:49.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,这可以让营养物质直接进入血液
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.30,0:05:49.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,This provides the nutrients directly into the bloodstream
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.10,0:05:54.97,辉中,,0,0,0,,通常用于各年龄段无法进食的病人
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.10,0:05:54.97,辉英,,0,0,0,,and is regularly used in people of all ages when they can not be fed by mouth.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:55.25,0:06:00.10,辉中,,0,0,0,,该过程跳过了进食与消化过程 因为消化系统是未激活状态
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.25,0:06:00.10,辉英,,0,0,0,,The process bypasses the eating and digestive tract which is inactive,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:00.10,0:06:04.62,辉中,,0,0,0,,液体会以每小时50毫升泵入体内
Dialogue: 2,0:06:00.10,0:06:04.62,辉英,,0,0,0,,with the fluids pumped in at about 50 ml per hour.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:04.77,0:06:11.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,这还要采取很多预防措施 比如要让居住舱内尽可能无菌
Dialogue: 2,0:06:04.77,0:06:11.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,There would also have to be many precautions taken such as making the inside of the habitat a sterile as possible
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.30,0:06:16.95,辉中,,0,0,0,,并使用隧道导管和抗生素注入活动导管
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.30,0:06:16.95,辉英,,0,0,0,,and using tunneled catheters and antibiotic-infused activity catheters
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.20,0:06:22.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,因为休眠时期任何感染都非常严重 甚至会致命
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.20,0:06:22.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,as any infection occurring during stasis could be very serious or even fatal
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.77,0:06:28.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,而飞船上医疗设备又极少 整个旅程就完犊子了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.77,0:06:28.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,and they would be very little in the way of any medical aid that could be done during the flight.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:28.34,0:06:32.47,辉中,,0,0,0,,但这种低温诱导的休眠有一个问题
Dialogue: 2,0:06:28.34,0:06:32.47,辉英,,0,0,0,,But there are issues with this kind of Hypothermic induced "stasis".
Dialogue: 1,0:06:32.65,0:06:38.00,辉中,,0,0,0,,虽然身体的代谢速率降低到70% 耗氧量更少
Dialogue: 2,0:06:32.65,0:06:38.00,辉英,,0,0,0,,Although the bodies metabolic rate drops by about 70% and uses less oxygen,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.10,0:06:45.45,辉中,,0,0,0,,大脑却并没有进入睡眠状态 这也是为什么电影中的乘客醒来时会觉得筋疲力尽
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.10,0:06:45.45,辉英,,0,0,0,,the brain never actually goes to sleep, which is why in the film "Passengers" they wake up feeling extremely tired.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:45.80,0:06:52.20,辉中,,0,0,0,,新的研究发现睡眠时大脑会排出白天积累的毒素
Dialogue: 2,0:06:45.80,0:06:52.20,辉英,,0,0,0,,New research is also finding that during sleep the brain flushes out toxins that build up during the day
Dialogue: 1,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.50,辉中,,0,0,0,,而这些毒素是阿兹海默症的诱因
Dialogue: 2,0:06:52.20,0:06:55.50,辉英,,0,0,0,,and which are thought to lead to the onset of Alzheimer's disease,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.65,0:07:01.32,辉中,,0,0,0,,而在休眠中大脑如果没有排毒 则在长期上是个麻烦
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.65,0:07:01.32,辉英,,0,0,0,,which if this doesn't happen in stasis could be a problem for long periods.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:01.50,0:07:08.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,经历低温疗法后的病人经常需要几天时间恢复体力与知觉
Dialogue: 2,0:07:01.50,0:07:08.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,Patients who currently undergo Therapeutic Hypothermia often take days to regain their strength and awareness,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:08.95,0:07:15.15,辉中,,0,0,0,,这对于宇航员来说是不行的 他们需要在几小时内就醒来并对警报作出回应
Dialogue: 2,0:07:08.95,0:07:15.15,辉英,,0,0,0,,not the sort of thing that an astronaut needs when they have to be awake and alert in just a few hours.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.67,0:07:17.90,辉中,,0,0,0,,为了预防肌肉萎缩
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.67,0:07:17.90,辉英,,0,0,0,,To help prevent muscle atrophy,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.97,0:07:23.30,辉中,,0,0,0,,可以使用很低能量的电脉冲刺激肌群
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.97,0:07:23.30,辉英,,0,0,0,,muscles could be electrically stimulated with very low-level electrical pulses to key muscle groups.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.60,0:07:29.07,辉中,,0,0,0,,还可以使用机械手操控 管理休眠中的乘员
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.60,0:07:29.07,辉英,,0,0,0,,Robot arms would also be able to manipulate and manage the crew during the time they are in stasis.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:29.07,0:07:34.27,辉中,,0,0,0,,又因为居住舱会比醒着的乘员需求的更小
Dialogue: 2,0:07:29.07,0:07:34.27,辉英,,0,0,0,,And because the living habitat is smaller than that required for a waking crew,
Dialogue: 1,0:07:34.32,0:07:40.22,辉中,,0,0,0,,就可以使用人工重力旋转整个休眠区
Dialogue: 2,0:07:34.32,0:07:40.22,辉英,,0,0,0,,artificially-induced gravity could be created by rotating the whole sleeping area.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:40.52,0:07:43.52,辉中,,0,0,0,,这个领域还有很多工作要完成
Dialogue: 2,0:07:40.52,0:07:43.52,辉英,,0,0,0,,There is a still a lot of work to be done in this field
Dialogue: 1,0:07:43.52,0:07:47.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,所以早期的火星任务不太可能会用上休眠技术
Dialogue: 2,0:07:43.52,0:07:47.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,so its highly unlikely that it would be used any of the early Mars mission
Dialogue: 1,0:07:47.97,0:07:53.42,辉中,,0,0,0,,但一旦这些问题被解决 那它就可能成为火星 甚至更远的任务中的标配
Dialogue: 2,0:07:47.97,0:07:53.42,辉英,,0,0,0,,but once the issues have been ironed out it could become a standard way to travel to Mars and beyond.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.72,0:07:57.70,辉中,,0,0,0,,长达数年的任务可能需要更长的苏醒期
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.72,0:07:57.70,辉英,,0,0,0,,Journeys running into years though would require longer wake up periods
Dialogue: 1,0:07:57.70,0:08:03.05,辉中,,0,0,0,,或者轮班制 比如保证总有1/3的乘员是苏醒状态
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.70,0:08:03.05,辉英,,0,0,0,,or a shift rotation where maybe 1/3 of the crew are awake at any one time.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.42,0:08:05.80,辉中,,0,0,0,,在这个技术成熟之前
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.42,0:08:05.80,辉英,,0,0,0,,By the time this becomes widely available
Dialogue: 1,0:08:05.80,0:08:09.82,辉中,,0,0,0,,我们可能已经有了更快的太空旅行技术
Dialogue: 2,0:08:05.80,0:08:09.82,辉英,,0,0,0,,we might even have developed quicker ways of getting around in space.
